## Edge cases

- **Trivial domain shift (S5 gate fail).** Refuse. Do not silently downgrade
  to a "soft clone" mode — there isn't one.
- **Zero proprietary slots (S4 gate fail).** Refuse.
- **Zero fidelity targets (S8 gate fail).** Refuse — without fidelity tests,
  there's no way to know the transposition preserved the mechanism.
- **Target dir already has conflicting code.** AskUserQuestion: archive existing
  to `<target-dir>.pre-twist/` or abort.
- **`/autobuild` partially completes.** Resume from the BUILD-LOG.md checkbox
  state on next invocation; do not regenerate the scaffold.
- **Slot stub accidentally pasted real impl.** Self-check Step 10 scans slot
  stubs for body length > 1 line; warns. The slot author can override by adding
  a `// LITERAL-IMPL-OK` marker after re-confirming via AskUserQuestion.
- **Verbatim-copy detection.** Scan scaffold for code blocks that match more
  than ~25 consecutive tokens from any file in `studies/<slug>/evidence/`. Any
  match is a hard fail — block the build until the copy is paraphrased.
- **GPL/AGPL source from `/blueprint` `--mode code`.** Re-surface the license
  warning here even if it was acked in `/blueprint`. Transpositions inherit the
  obligation if mechanism is copied; require AskUserQuestion ack again.

