## Dependencies

- **`/blueprint`** + **`/transpose`** — required upstream.
- **`/autoplan-full`** — output format compatibility (build-plan.md sections).
- **`/autobuild`** — execution; reads build-plan.md, lands commits, appends BUILD-LOG.md.
- **`/eval-harness`** — consumes `evals/fidelity/<slug>.jsonl`; runs mechanism-
  fidelity tests against the scaffold + slot fills.
- **`/verify-loop`** — invoked after `/autobuild` in `--mode full` to catch
  transposition gaps.
- **S12** — frontmatter chain `derived_from`.
- **S13** — `evals/fidelity/<slug>.jsonl` schema.
- **`lib/study-artifacts.ts`** — shared parser for S12 frontmatter (planned).

---

## Canonical examples

- **fingerspelling.xyz → TSL** (post-`/transpose`). Scaffold: core spaced-rep
  loop (STAY), TSL phoneme/handshape adapter (ADAPT), Thai UI module (REPLACE),
  proprietary slots `tsl-phoneme-encoder`, `tsl-pedagogy-ordering`, `tsl-eval-set`.
  Fidelity tests: "spaced-rep schedule preserves the source paper's retention
  curve" (cite paper) and "TSL-specific phonemes are 100% covered by the
  pedagogy graph" (target-domain invariant).

- **supertonic-v3** (inference → fine-tuning). Scaffold: model architecture +
  data loader (STAY), training-loop adapter (ADAPT), gradient-accumulation +
  checkpoint cadence (REPLACE), proprietary slots `training-strategy`,
  `regularization-schedule`, `eval-suite`. Fidelity tests: "fine-tuned model
  still passes the inference-only eval at ≥98% of baseline" and "gradient
  accumulation produces numerically equivalent updates to ungrouped step at
  micro-batch=1".

Use these as the v1 dogfood targets.
